back. Her robes seem to be whipping feverishly in the wind,
while her face and posture remain unphased. In the dark,
crystalline sky in the background, frowning, panicking
heavenly faces, stare hopelessly at her.
The glyph of strength is etched into a plaque below the painting,
along with the words:

THE STRENGTH TO SEVER THE TIES TO THE CAELUMAEDANI AND STAND ALONE
AS THE MORTAL RACE
~
